In this article, President Trump is interviewed and makes several remarks on various topics. He mentions that the UK is in turmoil due to Brexit and that NATO has not treated the US fairly in terms of financial contributions. He also expresses that he may speak to Boris Johnson and states that it is up to the people to decide if Theresa May should remain in power. Trump addresses the issue of America's allies and trade with the European Union, stating that the US cannot be taken advantage of. He mentions his upcoming meeting with Vladimir Putin and describes him as a competitor. Trump also briefly mentions Brett Kavanaugh's nomination and the positive reviews he has received. When asked about immigration and ICE, Trump emphasizes the importance of following the country's laws and coming to the US legally. He expresses support for ICE and criticizes the Democrats' stance on open borders.